.TH mlib_ImageColorErrorDiffusion3x3 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_ImageColorErrorDiffusion3x3 \- true color to indexed color conversion
using error diffusion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_ImageColorErrorDiffusion3x3\fR(\fBmlib_image *\fIdst\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_image *\fIsrc\fR, \fBconst mlib_s32 *\fIkernel\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIscale\fR,
     \fBconst void *\fIcolormap\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_ImageColorErrorDiffusion3x3()\fR function converts a true color
image to a pseudo color image with the method of error diffusion dithering.
The source image can be an \fBMLIB_BYTE\fR or \fBMLIB_SHORT\fR image with
three or four channels. The destination must be a single-channel
\fBMLIB_BYTE\fR or \fBMLIB_SHORT\fR image.
.sp
.LP
The last parameter, \fIcolormap\fR, is an internal data structure for
inverse color mapping. Create it by calling the
\fBmlib_ImageColorTrue2IndexInit()\fR function.
.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIdst\fR
.ad
.RS 12n
.rt
Pointer to destination or destination image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIsrc\fR
.ad
.RS 12n
.rt
Pointer to source or source image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIkernel\fR
.ad
.RS 12n
.rt
Pointer to the 3x3 error-distribution kernel, in row major order.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIscale\fR
.ad
.RS 12n
.rt
The scaling factor for kernel to convert the input integer coefficients
into floating-point coefficients:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
floating-point coefficient = integer coefficient * \e
2**(-scale)
.fi
.in -2

.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIcolormap\fR
.ad
.RS 12n
.rt
Internal data structure for inverse color mapping.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns
\fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
